  "finger_focus": "Sustained 80 WPM journalism",
  "guided": true,
  "tips": [
    {
      "type": "lead",
      "text": "No new keys today. This is newsroom work: a steady tempo held under pressure, where the longest word gets the same calm beat as the shortest. Three words, each repeated at one even pace."
    },
    {
      "type": "drop",
      "text": "Hands on the home row, thumbs over the space bar, eyes up. Repeat each word without rushing. A long word is no excuse to break stride; count it if you must: one, two, three, four."
    },
    {
      "type": "callout",
      "icon": "metronome",
      "title": "Even hands",
      "text": "On the wire, the copy goes out when it is due, ready or not. The hands that keep an even gap between keystrokes are the ones that make it. Hold the tempo and the long words stop frightening you."
    },
    {
      "type": "step",
      "kind": "drill",
      "unit": "reports",
      "baseReps": 5,
      "keys": ["r", "e", "p", "o", "t", "s"],
      "target": "reports reports reports reports reports",
      "finger": "blue",
      "title": "Rhythm: reports",
      "hint": "Repeat at one tempo: reports - reports - reports. Hold the gaps equal."
    },
    {
      "type": "step",
      "kind": "drill",
      "unit": "project",
      "baseReps": 4,
      "keys": ["p", "r", "o", "j", "e", "c", "t"],
      "target": "project project project project",
      "finger": "pink",
      "title": "Rhythm: project",
      "hint": "Repeat steadily, no jerks: project - project - project."
    },
    {
      "type": "step",
      "kind": "drill",
      "unit": "passengers",
      "baseReps": 3,
      "keys": ["p", "a", "s", "e", "n", "g", "r"],
      "target": "passengers passengers passengers",
      "finger": "pink",
      "title": "Rhythm: passengers",
      "hint": "Repeat evenly: passengers - passengers - passengers. Do not speed up at the end."
    },
    {
      "type": "p",
      "text": "Let the hand take even the long word in one motion, the way you read a place name you have set a hundred times. Even repetition is how the movement becomes automatic - and the automatic hand meets the deadline."
    },
    {
      "type": "pullquote",
      "text": "Loosen your shoulders and wrists, picture the metronome, and let rhythm carry the speed. Calm and even gets the copy out.",
      "by": "Eleanor Hayes, editor"
    },
    {
      "type": "p",
      "text": "All three done? Open the trainer below and take one clean run at the full lesson text. That run saves your progress and unlocks the next lesson."
    }
  ],
